# Problem Analysis

We are asked to prove or disprove the statement: "If P -> Q and Q -> R, then P -> R"

This is asking us to determine whether the following logical argument holds:
1. If P, then Q (P -> Q)
2. If Q, then R (Q -> R)  
3. Therefore, if P, then R (P -> R)

In other words, we're checking if this rule of inference - called "hypothetical syllogism" - is valid.
